    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-17T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="749"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5411: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Murmansk</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pierce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Murmansk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-17T14:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The evacuation Allied forces was carried out to the limit including British
                    consulate and the British signed [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] ship named <hi
                        rend="italic">Glory</hi>. Quiet restored at Murmansk as well as along the
                    coast, and the morale at the front position between two lakes north of
                    Petrozavodsk is favorable in spite of the fact flank railroad bridges in the
                    rear were destroyed but were repaired in as many days and the bandits caught and
                    punished. Latest information is [<hi rend="italic">received?</hi>] from
                    Archangel are [<hi rend="italic">is?</hi>] encouraging although refugees
                    continue to arrive from there. The Russian general commanding informs me that
                    some American citizens have been released from Soviet Russian territory and I
                    have replied requesting they be allowed to proceed here immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pierce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
